This paper is primarily focused on physical human-robot interaction (pHRI) and the development of an algorithm that allows the human to modulate both the actual and desired trajectories of the robot. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of constrained optimization and real-time implementation, which are relevant to the sub-categories of control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
